name: TheAtlantic
text:
RT @GrahamDavidA: I wrote last month that in North Carolina it was worth watching "countrypolitan" counties like Union as a bellwether: https://t.co/SLzWnKOwm9

So how did that play out? (1/4)

name: TheAtlantic
text: Some dispatches from this strange election purgatory, in the latest Atlantic Daily by @mimbsy: https://t.co/MdJEqj9HzP

name: TheAtlantic
text: "How long could this take? It might be a couple more hours. Or another day. A week of Tuesdays has already passed," @IsaacDovere reports from Wilmington: https://t.co/Id9yLclCdx

name: TheAtlantic
text: RT @AdrienneLaF: A quote for the ages: “What I am enjoying is that the most famously anti-science, anti-factual president of my lifetime is now being slowly taught mathematics, and the inescapable consequences of mathematics." @IsaacDovere's latest, just published https://t.co/hcd9yfIIKb

name: TheAtlantic
text:
RT @realcpaz: Lots of great detail in @IsaacDovere’s dispatch from Biden camp—read it:

“His aides are determined to give him at least one big, happy speech. They want to do it for a man who has spent 50 years dreaming of the presidency...”

https://t.co/5o5zng5uWj

name: TheAtlantic
text: International observers have been a part of American democracy for nearly two decades. The leader of the OSCE's observer mission told @YasmeenSerhan that this election is "definitely one for the memoirs." https://t.co/DlyZCSXgk7

name: TheAtlantic
text:
RT @JeffreyGoldberg: This @megangarber piece is definitive on the subject of Fox:
https://t.co/Pr5GUfXutP

name: TheAtlantic
text:
RT @JeffreyGoldberg: "Fox News, which spent years flattering Donald Trump and his fictions, is finishing what it started. The network that first helped bring Trump to political power is now working...to keep him there."
https://t.co/Pr5GUfXutP

name: TheAtlantic
text: At Steve Bannon’s Election Night party, bravado reigned. But reality quickly caught up with the Trumpism diehards, @mckaycoppins writes: https://t.co/BWonLnzJ2L

name: TheAtlantic
text:
RT @DKThomp: I wrote about two stories of the 2020 electorate: the depolarization of race and the polarization of place 

https://t.co/GMxeIu7uFC

In several states, non-white Americans voted a bit more like Republicans, and rich suburbs voted more like liberal cities.

name: TheAtlantic
text:
RT @AdrienneLaF: "Oh, he’s gonna win. One hundred percent.”

“You’re that confident?” 

“Absolutely.”

“And if it goes the other way…”

“I’ll eat my shoe. We’ll do it in a livestream.”

In which @mckaycoppins gets kicked out of Steve Bannon’s Election Night party: https://t.co/hFJuBHYG82

name: TheAtlantic
text: RT @PeterAtlantic: Despite all the COVID cases at the White House (Chief of Staff Mark Meadows is the latest), few if any West Wing aides in the press and comms areas on Election Night were wearing masks. Re-upping our story from August. https://t.co/nqfAS26xWZ

name: TheAtlantic
text:
Breaking: Joe Biden has defeated Donald Trump in the presidential race. 

Now Biden will turn toward repairing a badly broken country. But if anyone can put America back together, @FranklinFoer writes, it’s Joe Biden. https://t.co/Kzp6reB0Ob

name: TheAtlantic
text: "Harris’s ascent to the vice presidency is certainly a reflection of what’s possible. She has accomplished something that no other Black woman has," @jemelehill writes: https://t.co/ia7bcXPowX

name: TheAtlantic
text: "After four years of dread and shame, this is a moment for hope and pride. America stopped an authoritarian populist from destroying its democratic institutions," @Yascha_Mounk writes: https://t.co/9BM2e53g7j

name: TheAtlantic
text: RT @jemelehill: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris. I wrote about what that means for black women https://t.co/HyKmgQX5hW

name: TheAtlantic
text: RT @AdrienneLaF: "Eighteen months ago, launching his presidential campaign in Philadelphia, in a nod to the ideals enshrined in the United States Constitution, Joe Biden said, 'Everyone knows who Donald Trump is; we have to let them know who we are.' We did." https://t.co/67mhqMh128

name: TheAtlantic
text: RT @danteramos: “Some might think that breaking barriers means you start off on one side of the barrier,” said [Kamala] Harris, who was running for president at the time, “and then you just turn up on the other side of the barrier. No, there’s *breaking* involved.” https://t.co/lXxn9GeG4H

name: TheAtlantic
text: RT @nora_kelly: .@FranklinFoer: "The nation is desperate for a parental figure to cultivate renewal amid ruin; shattered institutions will require an almost irrational faith in healing ... What’s needed is the urgency of someone watching time as it melts away." https://t.co/MWERoG2nso

name: TheAtlantic
text: "With Pennsylvania having completed its blue shift into Joe Biden’s column, the election is effectively over, and the president has been defeated. The exact contours of the loss aren’t clear yet, but the ultimate outcome is," @GrahamDavidA writes: https://t.co/C9pe9WyWsg

name: TheAtlantic
text: 1/3 Joe Biden has defeated Donald Trump in the presidential race. We examined how Biden has changed, and what a lam… https://t.co/DhKaInJovM

name: TheAtlantic
text:
2/3 "Where past presidents exuded supreme self-confidence, with little doubt about how the world should perceive them, Biden feels as if he needs to claw his way into history,“ @FranklinFoer wrote last month.
https://t.co/tW4qzQE67h

name: TheAtlantic
text: 3/3 Last month, @davidfrum laid out four risks of a lame-duck Trump presidency, and how to guard against them: https://t.co/8eKJIkxgDS
